ZH: 我不能保证每天都准时到达，但我承诺尽力遵守时间安排。
EN: I can't guarantee to arrive on time every day, but I promise to do my best to stick to the schedule.

ZH: 加入这个项目，你必须遵守项目组的承诺。
EN: To join this project, you must adhere to the team's promises.

ZH: 他发誓要实现他的所有承诺。
EN: He swore to fulfill all his promises.

ZH: 他的父母不希望他轻易地承诺结婚。
EN: His parents do not want him to make a commitment to marriage easily.

ZH: 他承诺会为这个计划提供全部资金支持。
EN: He promised to provide full financial support for this plan.

ZH: 我们都很失望，因为他没有遵守他的承诺。
EN: We were all disappointed because he didn't keep his promise.

ZH: 她承诺会努力改正她的错误。
EN: She promised to make efforts to correct her mistakes.

ZH: 他做出了一个终身承诺，和她一起生活下去。
EN: He made a lifelong commitment to live with her.

ZH: 作为一个市长，我给你我的郑重承诺，一切都是为了市民的福利。
EN: As the mayor, I give you my solemn promise that everything is for the welfare of the citizens.

ZH: 这个公司承诺保护员工的隐私。
EN: This company commits to protecting the privacy of its employees.

ZH: 在这个项目中，我们需要大家共同承诺。
EN: In this project, we need everyone to make a shared commitment.

ZH: 我相信你的承诺，但我也需要看到实际行动。
EN: I trust your promise, but I also need to see concrete actions.

ZH: 我向你保证，我对这个问题的关注是真诚的。
EN: I assure you that my concern for this issue is genuine.

ZH: 我的父母总是告诫我不要随随便便地做空洞的承诺。
EN: My parents always warn me not to make hollow promises.

ZH: 这个合同中列明了雇主和雇员之间的责任和承诺。
EN: The contract specifies the responsibilities and commitments between the employer and the employee.

ZH: 我以我的名誉作担保，承诺这个产品的质量。
EN: I vouch for the quality of this product with my honor.

ZH: 他的承诺比任何人都可靠。
EN: His commitment is more reliable than anyone else's.

ZH: 别把你所做的承诺看得太轻松。
EN: Don't take your promises lightly.

ZH: 我深信他会履行他的诺言。
EN: I firmly believe that he will fulfill his promises.

ZH: 如果你不想履行你的承诺，就别轻易地做出承诺。
EN: If you don't want to fulfill your commitments, don't make promises lightly.
